<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="97" type="phenology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="97">Phenology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="97">It was observed with flower and fruit at the same time from October to December and June to July.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="97" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="97">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="97">
This new species is named in honor of Mr. Fang Ding (1924-2017) for his contributions to studies of the family 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Acanthaceae" genus="Rungia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="97" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Acanthaceae</taxonomicName>
from Guangxi, China. He was the co-author of the account of family 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Acanthaceae" genus="Rungia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="97" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Acanthaceae</taxonomicName>
for &quot;Flora of Guangxi&quot; and has published 37 new taxa of 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Acanthaceae" genus="Rungia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="97" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Acanthaceae</taxonomicName>
from Guangxi (
<bibRefCitation author="Fang, D" editor="Li, SG" journalOrPublisher="Guangxi Science and Technology Publishing House, Nanning" pageId="0" pageNumber="97" pagination="763 - 766" refId="B6" refString="Fang, D, Deng, YF, 2017. Acanthaceae. In: Li, SG, Ed., Flora of Guangxi 4. Guangxi Science and Technology Publishing House, Nanning: 763 - 766" title="Acanthaceae." volumeTitle="Flora of Guangxi 4." year="2017">Fang and Deng 2017</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="97" type="vernacular name">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="97">Vernacular name.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="97">
<normalizedToken originalValue="方鼎孩儿草">方鼎孩儿草</normalizedToken>
(Chinese pinyin: 
<normalizedToken originalValue="fāng">fang</normalizedToken>
<normalizedToken originalValue="dǐng">dǐng</normalizedToken>
<normalizedToken originalValue="hái">hai</normalizedToken>
<normalizedToken originalValue="ér">er</normalizedToken>
<normalizedToken originalValue="cǎo">cǎo</normalizedToken>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="97" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="97">Distribution and habitat.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="97">This species is currently known from three localities in Napo County of Guangxi Province. It grows close to stream sides in evergreen forest on limestone at elevations of 600 to 1200 m.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="97" type="conservation status">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="97">Conservation status.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="97">
During the field investigations, only three scattered populations of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Z. L. Lin, Y. F. Deng &amp; Y. H. Tan" authorityYear="2022" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Acanthaceae" genus="Rungia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Rungia fangdingiana" order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="97" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fangdingiana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">Rungia fangdingiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were discovered, which all grow in forest on limestone in Napo county. Because of its narrow distribution (extent of occurrence &lt;20,000 km2), limited locations (&lt;10), with an estimated population size of &lt;1000 mature individuals, and there is continuing decline estimated in quality of habitat and number of locations due to human activities as the localities are not protected, it should be assessed as Vulnerable (VU) (B1ab(iii)(iv)) according to the IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria (
<bibRefCitation author="Hu, JQ" journalOrPublisher="Vol 19. Science Press, Beijing; Missouri Botanical Garden Press, St. Louis" pageId="0" pageNumber="97" refId="B14" refString="IUCN (2012) IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria. Version 3.1. 2nd Edn. IUCN Species Survival Commission, Gland &amp; Cambridge." year="2011">IUCN 2012</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Hu, JQ" journalOrPublisher="Vol 19. Science Press, Beijing; Missouri Botanical Garden Press, St. Louis" pageId="0" pageNumber="97" publicationUrl="http://www.iucnredlist.org/documents/RedListGuidelines.pdf" refId="B15" refString="2022. . http://www.iucnredlist.org/documents/RedListGuidelines.pdf" url="http://www.iucnredlist.org/documents/RedListGuidelines.pdf" year="2022">2022</bibRefCitation>
). However, the area around the localities of this new species is poorly investigated, and further rigorous investigations are necessary to confirm this assessment.
</paragraph>
